entries.femaleVariant: "What now?"
Now I go back, find Misty and we do somethin' to make me feel alive again.
What now?
What now, Jack?
Catch a fright back there? That you wouldn't make it back?
Hazards of the profession.
Risks come with the job, Jack.
Catch a real fright back there?
<mothertongue l="mex" m="Ahí luego." b="Don't forget to let Dex know we got his toy for him. " a=""/>
Nah, shit like that don't cross my mind. But I am grateful for comin' through.
Ducked in time to avoid death's sweeping scythe, again. Only right to celebrate. Even though we get to do that lots…
No begging, no debt, no corpo strings attached. And the Flathead's ours.
That's the way to do biz, V.
Couldn't agree more.
Sometime it is, sometimes it isn't. Got lucky today.
Tough to argue.
Sometimes, yeah. Depends.
Ahhhh, I love this town. The city of endless opportunity. And brotherly hate.
It's 'cause I'm right, always. Nice of you to notice.
Ain't you a ray of sunshine. But, V, it ain't a matter of luck. You decide. Remember that.
<mothertongue l="mex" m="cojones" b="But if you got the " a=" and know how to use 'em, you can do damn near anything."/>
Unless you catch a bullet, stray or not.
Even then you go out with a bang! And the street'll talk, the street'll remember. Win-win.
You're a hell of an optimist.
You could make heaps more eddies as a motivational speaker.
<kiroshi l="mex" o="Jórate, güey" t="Fuck you, man." b="" a=""/>
Coulda shot us up good back there – no two ways about it.
